Simple to-do list application in Java using Spring Boot for the backend and Thymeleaf for the frontend. The application will have the following functionalities:
Task CRUD: Create, read, update and delete tasks.
Simple Web Interface: To manage tasks.
H2 Database: To store tasks.
Project Structure
Task: Class that represents a task.
TaskRepository: Interface that manages the persistence of tasks.
TaskController: Controller that manages HTTP requests related to tasks.
Thymeleaf Templates: For the user interface.
Steps to Create the Project
Create the Project with Spring Boot:

Use Spring Initializr to generate the project with the dependencies:
Spring Web
Spring Data JPA
H2 Database
Thymeleaf
Package Structure:

com.example.todolist (main package)
controller (for the controller)
model (for the Task class)
repository (for the repository)

Code Explanation
Task: Class that represents the tasks in the application. Each task has a title, description, and completion status.

TaskRepository: JPA interface to perform CRUD operations on the database for tasks.

TaskController: Controller that manages the routes to create, view, update, and delete tasks.

Thymeleaf Templates: Used to render the user interface.

H2 Database: In-memory database used for data storage during development.